    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/2085: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 17, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. For Murphy from the Under Secretary. Your 16, January 16, 5 p.m. I think it
                    would be highly desirable for you to remain in Lisbon until the conversations
                    mentioned in your telegram have been concluded. Please inform the Department by
                    telegram of the results.</p>
                <p>The information contained in your telegram of January 14<note n="31a"
                        xml:id="d171fn31a">Telegram No. 14. <ref target="#pg_206">p.
                        206</ref>.</note> has been exceptionally valuable to the Department and we
                    are most gratified with the results of your trip. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
